<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ArtQuest: Explore Art</title>
    <style>
        /* General Styles */
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
            color: #333;
        }

        /* Navigation Bar */
        header {
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 15px 30px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
        }

        .logo h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: normal;
        }

        nav ul {
            display: flex;
            gap: 20px;
            list-style: none;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        nav ul li a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 16px;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }

        nav ul li a:hover {
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        /* Hero Section */
        .hero {
            background-image: url('hero-background.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            height: 400px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            color: black;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .hero-content h2 {
            font-size: 48px;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .hero-content p {
            font-size: 20px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        .cta-button {
            background-color: #e74c3c;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 18px;
        }

        .cta-button:hover {
            background-color: #c0392b;
        }

        /* Featured Art Section */
        .featured-art {
            padding: 50px 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .featured-art h2 {
            font-size: 36px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .art-gallery {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-around;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 20px;
        }

        .art-item {
            background-color: white;
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            width: 30%;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .art-item img {
            width: 100%;
            display: block;
        }

        .art-item h3 {
            margin: 15px 0 5px;
            font-size: 22px;
        }

        .art-item p {
            margin: 0 0 15px;
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #777;
        }

        .art-item:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }

        /* Description Styles */
        .description {
            margin: 10px 0;
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #444;
            line-height: 1.5;
            padding: 0 15px;
            text-align: justify;
        }

        /* Footer */
        footer {
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px 0;
        }

        footer p {
            margin: 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="logo">
            <h1>ArtQuest: How Well Do You Know Art?</h1>
        </div>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="/home">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="/gallery">Gallery</a></li>
                <li><a href="/quiz" class="active">Quiz</a></li>
                <li><a href="/history">History</a></li>
                <li><a href="/aboutus">About us</a></li>
                <li><a href="/Result">Result</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h2>Discover the Beauty of Art</h2>
            <p>Explore a vast collection of stunning artwork from renowned artists worldwide.</p> <br> <br> <br> <br> <br> 
            <a href="#gallery" class="cta-button">Explore the Gallery</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Enhanced Gallery Section -->
    <section class="featured-art" id="gallery">
        <br> <br> <br> 
        <h2>ArtQuest Gallery</h2>
        <p>Browse through some of the finest pieces of art from various artists. Click on any piece to learn more about it!</p>
        <div class="art-gallery">
            <div class="art-item" onclick="toggleDescription(this)">
                <img src="images/one.png" alt="Artwork 1">
                <h3>The Starry Night</h3>
                <p>Vincent van Gogh</p>
                <div class="description" style="display: none;">
                    <p>A masterpiece painted in 1889, depicting a swirling night sky filled with stars above a quiet village. This iconic work reflects van Gogh's emotional turmoil and innovative use of color and brushwork.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="art-item" onclick="toggleDescription(this)">
                <img src="images/two.png" alt="Artwork 2">
                <h3>The Persistence of Memory</h3>
                <p>Salvador Dal√≠</p>
                <div class="description" style="display: none;">
                    <p>Created in 1931, this surreal painting features melting clocks draped over a desolate landscape. It explores themes of time, dreams, and the unconscious mind, becoming a hallmark of surrealism.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="art-item" onclick="toggleDescription(this)">
                <img src="images/three.png" alt="Artwork 3">
                <h3>Girl with a Pearl Earring</h3>
                <p>Johannes Vermeer</p>
                <div class="description" style="display: none;">
                    <p>Painted around 1665, this artwork is often referred to as the 'Mona Lisa of the North.' It features a girl in a dark background, turning to gaze at the viewer, adorned with an exotic turban and a large pearl earring.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="art-item" onclick="toggleDescription(this)">
                <img src="images/four.png" alt="Artwork 4">
                <h3>The Scream</h3>
                <p>Edvard Munch</p>
                <div class="description" style="display: none;">
                    <p>This iconic 1893 painting captures an agonized figure against a turbulent sky, symbolizing existential dread. It is considered a major work of expressionism, reflecting Munch's personal anxieties and emotions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="art-item" onclick="toggleDescription(this)">
                <img src="images/five.png" alt="Artwork 5">
                <h3>Mona Lisa</h3>
                <p>Leonardo da Vinci</p>
                <div class="description" style="display: none;">
                    <p>Created between 1503 and 1506, this portrait of a woman with a serene expression has become one of the most famous artworks in history. Its mysterious background and the subject's ambiguous smile have captivated viewers for centuries.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="art-item" onclick="toggleDescription(this)">
                <img src="images/six.png" alt="Artwork 6">
                <h3>The Kiss</h3>
                <p>Gustav Klimt</p>
                <div class="description" style="display: none;">
                    <p>This 1907-1908 work features a couple embracing, enveloped in elaborate robes adorned with gold leaf. Klimt's use of color and pattern symbolizes intimacy and passion, making it a defining piece of the Art Nouveau movement.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Art Gallery. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        function toggleDescription(element) {
            const description = element.querySelector('.description');
            description.style.display = description.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
